CatDescriptText: Mrs. Luella White, 1541 Colwell Street was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 19, 1958, pg. 9 with question: "Do you think that a business recession has hit the United States? If so, how has it affected you?" answer reads: "I really do.  Financially, I can't do the things that I used to do and the main reason is because of the high cost of living.  Things are really up now.  Before, I could save a little, but I can't do it now."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Luella White wearing light colored hat and striped dress, standing on Market Street, Downtown
